TY  - JOUR
AU  - Beach, Charles M.
AU  - Davidson, Russell
T1  - Distribution-Free Statistical Inference with Lorenz Curves and Income Shares
PY  - 1983
Y1  - 1983/10/01
DO  - 10.2307/2297772
JO  - The Review of Economic Studies
JA  - Rev Econ Stud
VL  - 50
IS  - 4
SP  - 723
EP  - 735
SN  - 0034-6527
AB  - The paper considers the problem of statistical inference with estimated Lorenz curves and income shares. The full variance-covariance structure of the (asymptotic) normal distribution of a vector of Lorenz curve ordinates is derived and shown to depend only on conditional first and second moments that can be estimated consistently without prior specification of the population density underlying the sample data. Lorenz curves and income shares can thus be used as tools for statistical inference instead of simply as descriptive statistics.
Y2  - 3/25/2024
UR  - https://doi.org/10.2307/2297772
ER  - 



